  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of medical care to poor and IDP patients in Homs</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Homs governorate is experiencing severe health challenges under the current deteriorated situation in Syria.  Secondary and Tertiary health care as well as the first Aid and trauma management care  services  are almost unavailable and access to medicines and hospital care for IDPs and the residents in certain areas in Homs city is steadily decreasing.
This project will provide medical care to the poor and IDPs in Homs, and Primary Health Care to people in Hard to Reach and Besieged Areas. The project will target patients in need for hospitalization and tertiary care of which , most of them are from most vulnerable groups (IDPs, women) who can&#x2019;t afford the cost of surgeries and treatment, and it will fill the gap of shortage of public hospitals in Homs.
The project will support the following categories:
	Hosting communities in Homs City (30% of supported beneficiaries)
	IDPs in Homs City (50% of supported beneficiaries)
	Injuries and PIN who are located in HTR and Besieged areas (20% of supported beneficiaries)
Activities will include provision of the following lifesaving services:
1-	Casks stay and treatment for 250 infants
2-	Accommodation at hospitals for 750 patients.
3-	General surgeries for 515 patients. (Mostly for those who injured during the current crisis and considered part of lifesaving surgeries).
4-	Orthopedic surgeries for 300 patients.
5-	Neurologic surgeries for 100 patients. 
The total number of the patients is 1915 as following: 515 general operations, 300 Orthopedic operations 100 neurological operations, 750 hospital accommodation and 250 casks.</narrative>
  </description>
